    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-15T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-15T22:00:00-05:00" n="56"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">600.939/247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-16T12:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 16, 1938—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 16—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>535. Department’s 281, August 11, 7 p.m., via Peiping, hides and skins embargo.
                    In view of the information given in Tientsin’s 154, August 10, 3 p.m.,<note
                        n="58" xml:id="d56fn58">Not printed.</note> and 155, August 15, noon, we
                    propose to take no further action unless Tientsin finds that the modification of
                    the embargo fails satisfactorily to alleviate the restriction on American
                    exporters.</p>
                <p>Please repeat to Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
